PRIORITY: P0 (Critical)

Immediate Actions (First 30 minutes):

1. Incident Commander: Myself (coordination)
2. War Room: Zoom + Slack #incident-2024-10-21
3. Team Assembly:
   - @devops-infrastructure-specialist: Infrastructure investigation
   - @database-implementation-specialist: Database query analysis
   - @backend-architect: Application code review
   - @web-performance-specialist: Performance profiling

Initial Triage (Update every 15 min):
- [09:15] Incident detected via monitoring alerts
- [09:20] Team assembled, investigation started
- [09:30] Root cause identified: Database connection pool exhaustion
- [09:35] Hotfix deployed: Increased pool size 20 → 100
- [09:40] Performance restored: Response times 15s → 1.2s ✅

Post-Incident Actions:

Short-term (Next 24 hours):
- Monitor metrics closely
- Document incident timeline
- Brief stakeholders on resolution

Long-term (Next week):
- Post-mortem meeting (@devops-infrastructure-specialist lead)
- Permanent fix: Auto-scaling connection pools
- Improved monitoring: Connection pool alerts
- Runbook update: Connection exhaustion procedures

Lessons Learned Documentation:
- Root cause: Connection pool configuration inadequate for traffic spike
- Detection time: 5 minutes (good)
- Resolution time: 25 minutes (acceptable)
- Improvement: Earlier alerting on connection pool utilization

Status: Incident RESOLVED
Next review: Post-mortem in 2 days"
```

